			<common:generalComment xml:lang="en">Coal is an abundant natural resource used as a source of energy and a chemical source from which numerous synthetic compounds can be derived. It is also used in the production of coke for metallurgical processes. Coal is a major source of energy in the production of electrical power using steam generation. It is a non-clastic sedimentary rock, the fossilized remains of plants, in flammable black and brownish-black tones. Its main element is carbon, but it can also contain elements such as hydrogen, sulfur, and oxygen.</common:generalComment>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="zh">煤炭是一种丰富的自然资源，既可用作能源，也可用作化学原料，从中可以提炼出许多合成化合物。煤还可用于生产冶金过程所需的焦炭。煤炭是利用蒸汽发电的主要能源。煤是一种非碎屑沉积岩，是植物的化石残骸，呈易燃的黑色和棕黑色。其主要元素是碳，但也可能含有氢、硫和氧等元素。</common:generalComment>
